Tk::RotatingGauge
===================

This perl module provides a new Tk widget representing a gauge where the
current value always stays at the same place. Think about your old
mileage counters...



INSTALLATION
============

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


Or, using Module::Builder:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install



SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
=========================

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Tk::RotatingGauge

You can also look for information at:
  . Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Tk-RotatingGauge
  . CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Tk-RotatingGauge
  . AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Tk-RotatingGauge
  . CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Tk-RotatingGauge



